<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>John Thorndike</strong></span> bought his farm in Athens, Ohio, in the 1970s, when he was writing and gardening. He enjoys the same activities today, except that he has thirty tomato plants &mdash; instead of three thousand &mdash; and more time to write. He is the author of <em>The Last of His Mind: A Year in the Shadow of Alzheimer&rsquo;s</em> (Swallow Press), which the <em>Washington Post </em>named as one of the best books of 2009.</p><a href="/contributors/john-thorndike" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
